Soil

bulk <- read_csv(here("NCOS_Bulk_Den_Samples.csv")) %>%  # this line reads in the csv
  drop_na() 
## Rows: 200 Columns: 7
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (1): Zone
## dbl (6): GPS_point_#, Sample, dried_mass_g, volume_mL, bulk_density_g_cm_3, ...
## 
## i Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## i Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
bulk_avg <- bulk %>% 
  janitor::clean_names() %>% 
  group_by(zone, gps_point_number) %>% 
  summarize(mean_bulk = mean(bulk_density_g_cm_3))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'zone'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
bulk_sum <- bulk_avg %>% 
  group_by(zone) %>% 
  summarize(min = min(mean_bulk),
            max = max(mean_bulk),
            sd = sd(mean_bulk),
            mean = mean(mean_bulk),
            sample_size = n())

kable(bulk_sum,
      col.names = c("Zone", "Min. Den. (g/cm^3)", "Max. Den. (g/cm^3)", "Standard Dev.", "Mean Den. (g/cm^3)", "Sample Size")) %>% 
  kable_classic()
Zone Min. Den. (g/cm^3) Max. Den. (g/cm^3) Standard Dev. Mean Den. (g/cm^3) Sample Size
F1 1.1333696 1.877806 0.1659644 1.579795 35
F3 0.7710282 2.622702 0.5210165 1.586258 35

Artemisia

art <- read_csv(here("artemisia_transects.csv")) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names()
## Rows: 62 Columns: 4
## -- Column specification --------------------------------------------------------
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (1): Zone
## dbl (3): Artemisia #, GPS Point #, Longest Branch (cm)
## 
## i Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## i Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
art_sum <- art %>% 
  group_by(zone) %>% 
  summarize(min = min(longest_branch_cm),
            max = max(longest_branch_cm),
            sd = sd(longest_branch_cm),
            mean = mean(longest_branch_cm))

kable(art_sum,
      col.names = c("Zone", "Min. Branch Length (cm)", "Max. Branch Length (cm)", "Standard Dev.", "Mean Branch Length (cm)")) %>% 
  kable_classic()

T-Test

f1 <- bulk_avg %>% 
  filter(zone == "F1")

f3 <- bulk_avg %>% 
  filter(zone == "F3")

bulk_test <- t.test(f1$mean_bulk, f3$mean_bulk)

bulk_test
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  f1$mean_bulk and f3$mean_bulk
## t = -0.069917, df = 40.829, p-value = 0.9446
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.1931480  0.1802234
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  1.579795  1.586258

Read in the shapes and set coordinates

soil_sf <- read_sf(here("gis_data", "bulk_density.shp")) %>% 
  janitor::clean_names() %>% 
  mutate(cid = case_when(
    cid == 0 ~ "F1",
    cid == 1 ~ "F3"
  ))

zone_sf <- read_sf(here("gis_data", "zones.shp")) %>% 
  select(Zone)

art_sf <- read_sf(here("gis_data", "all_artemisia_correct.shp"))

# change coordinate reference systems (crs)

zone_sf <- st_transform(zone_sf, st_crs(soil_sf))
ggplot()+
  geom_sf(data = zone_sf)+
  geom_sf(data = art_sf, aes(color = branch_cm))

Clip Data

soil_clip <- soil_sf %>% 
  st_intersection(zone_sf)
## Warning: attribute variables are assumed to be spatially constant throughout all
## geometries
art_clip <- art_sf %>% 
  st_intersection(zone_sf)
## Warning: attribute variables are assumed to be spatially constant throughout all
## geometries

Variogram

soil_vgm <- gstat::variogram(bulk_den ~ 1,
                             data = soil_clip)

plot(soil_vgm)

soil_vgm_fit <- gstat::fit.variogram(soil_vgm,
                                     model = vgm(model = "Exp",
                                                 nugget = 10,
                                                 sill = 1000,
                                                 range = 0.01))
## Warning in gstat::fit.variogram(soil_vgm, model = vgm(model = "Exp", nugget =
## 10, : No convergence after 200 iterations: try different initial values?
plot(soil_vgm, soil_vgm_fit)

Interpolation by Kriging

zone_grid <- st_bbox(zone_sf) %>% 
  st_as_stars() %>% 
  st_set_crs(st_crs(zone_sf)) %>% 
  st_crop(zone_sf)
## st_as_s2(): dropping Z and/or M coordinate
soil_krige <- krige(bulk_den ~ 1, 
                    soil_clip,
                    zone_grid,
                    model = soil_vgm_fit)
## [using ordinary kriging]
plot(soil_krige)

krige_df <- as.data.frame(soil_krige) %>% 
  st_as_sf(coords = c("x", "y")) %>% 
  drop_na(var1.pred) %>% 
  st_set_crs(st_crs(art_clip))

ggplot()+
  geom_sf(data = krige_df,
          aes(color = var1.pred))+
  scale_color_gradient(low = "wheat", high = 'chartreuse4')+
  geom_sf(data = art_clip)

Spatial Join

art_soil <- art_clip %>% 
  st_join(krige_df, st_is_within_distance, dist = 0.5) %>% 
  group_by(ID, CID) %>% 
  summarise(branch_cm = mean(branch_cm),
            bulk_den = mean(var1.pred))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'ID'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
